WEBVTT

1
00:00:07.541 --> 00:00:08.901
‐ Previously on
"Resident Alien"...

2
00:00:09.710 --> 00:00:10.753
‐ I think this alien's here
to kill everybody.

3
00:00:10.777 --> 00:00:12.021
‐ There's my device.

4
00:00:12.045 --> 00:00:13.990
‐ That's in the glacier.
You can't go there.

5
00:00:14.014 --> 00:00:15.892
Harry. don't go!
It's too dangerous.

6
00:00:15.916 --> 00:00:18.228
‐ These humans believe they're
nothing without one another.

7
00:00:18.252 --> 00:00:19.996
‐ I want you to be comfortable
enough with me

8
00:00:20.020 --> 00:00:21.164
to tell me that I'm wrong.

9
00:00:21.188 --> 00:00:23.433
I want a partner
who challenges me.

10
00:00:23.457 --> 00:00:25.468
‐ You earn respect through
your actions. Deputy.

11
00:00:25.492 --> 00:00:26.936
‐ Well. how about this
for an action?

12
00:00:26.960 --> 00:00:28.171
I quit!

13
00:00:28.195 --> 00:00:29.873
‐ I wanted to go
to the Olympics.

14
00:00:29.897 --> 00:00:31.007
and then this happened.

15
00:00:31.031 --> 00:00:32.609
It was my second mogul run.

16
00:00:32.633 --> 00:00:34.177
It was before the jump.
and I couldn't stop.

17
00:00:34.201 --> 00:00:37.180
I landed. and I heard
a bunch of bones crack.

18
00:00:37.204 --> 00:00:39.015
They said I could've
lost my leg.

19
00:00:39.039 --> 00:00:40.950
‐ Once I eradicate humanity.

20
00:00:40.974 --> 00:00:42.619
I'll return to my planet a hero.

21
00:00:42.643 --> 00:00:45.221
I'm so close
to completing my mission.

22
00:00:45.245 --> 00:00:47.390
‐ Something initiated this.

23
00:00:47.414 --> 00:00:49.392
The ship is tethered. Holy shit.

24
00:00:49.416 --> 00:00:50.760
I know where the alien is!

25
00:00:50.784 --> 00:00:52.595
‐ Harry?

26
00:00:52.619 --> 00:00:54.631
Don't move.

27
00:00:54.655 --> 00:00:55.889
Aah!

28
00:00:56.590 --> 00:00:59.669
[Fleet Foxes'
"Helplessness Blues"]

29
00:00:59.693 --> 00:01:00.803
♪ ♪

30
00:01:00.827 --> 00:01:04.974
‐ ♪ I was raised up believing ♪

31
00:01:04.998 --> 00:01:08.811
♪ I was somehow unique ♪

32
00:01:08.835 --> 00:01:11.414
♪ Like a snowflake ♪

33
00:01:11.438 --> 00:01:13.449
♪ Distinct among snowflakes ♪

34
00:01:13.473 --> 00:01:16.519
♪ Unique in each way
you can see ♪

35
00:01:16.543 --> 00:01:20.223
♪ And now after some thinking ♪

36
00:01:20.247 --> 00:01:25.194
♪ I'd say I'd rather be ♪

37
00:01:25.218 --> 00:01:27.297
♪ A functioning cog ♪

38
00:01:27.321 --> 00:01:29.399
♪ In some great machinery ♪

39
00:01:29.423 --> 00:01:32.035
♪ Serving something beyond me ♪

40
00:01:32.059 --> 00:01:36.139
♪ But I don't. I don't ♪

41
00:01:36.163 --> 00:01:40.009
♪ Know what that will be ♪

42
00:01:40.033 --> 00:01:42.045
♪ I'll get back ♪

43
00:01:42.069 --> 00:01:46.015
♪ To you someday soon ♪

44
00:01:46.039 --> 00:01:48.051
♪ You will see ♪

45
00:01:48.075 --> 00:01:51.955
♪ ♪

46
00:01:51.979 --> 00:01:53.056
[thunder rolls]

47
00:01:53.080 --> 00:01:56.292
[Brown Bird's "Bilgewater"]

48
00:01:56.316 --> 00:01:59.662
[laidback acoustic strumming]

49
00:01:59.686 --> 00:02:02.356
♪ ♪

50
00:02:03.023 --> 00:02:05.325
‐ [coughing]

51
00:02:07.527 --> 00:02:09.038
‐ D'arcy.

52
00:02:09.062 --> 00:02:11.474
‐ Ugh. ow. ‐ Harry?

53
00:02:11.498 --> 00:02:12.942
‐ [sighs]

54
00:02:12.966 --> 00:02:15.278
‐ Oh. thank God. We're all okay.

55
00:02:15.302 --> 00:02:16.446
‐ Okay?

56
00:02:16.470 --> 00:02:18.982
We fell into a crevasse.
This is a death trap.

57
00:02:19.006 --> 00:02:20.583
‐ Sorry I said anything.

58
00:02:20.607 --> 00:02:22.719
‐ [sighs]

59
00:02:22.743 --> 00:02:24.520
[grunts] I can't move it.

60
00:02:24.544 --> 00:02:26.189
I'm too weak.

61
00:02:26.213 --> 00:02:27.523
‐ Harry. your leg.

62
00:02:27.547 --> 00:02:28.891
‐ Oh. whoa. whoa!

63
00:02:28.915 --> 00:02:30.693
No sudden movements.

64
00:02:30.717 --> 00:02:32.562
‐ I'm not going anywhere.

65
00:02:32.586 --> 00:02:33.663
My leg is trapped.

66
00:02:33.687 --> 00:02:34.897
‐ We need help.

67
00:02:34.921 --> 00:02:36.532
‐ This whole sheet of ice
could cave in at any second.

68
00:02:36.556 --> 00:02:38.468
What were you doing up here?

69
00:02:38.492 --> 00:02:40.269
I told you not to go up
on the glacier.

70
00:02:40.293 --> 00:02:42.038
‐ It is your fault.

71
00:02:42.062 --> 00:02:44.273
The ice caved in
because you are too heavy.

72
00:02:44.297 --> 00:02:45.742
‐ Okay. we're leaving him.

73
00:02:45.766 --> 00:02:47.744
‐ I guess glaciers aren't
a part of a cell plan. guys.

74
00:02:47.768 --> 00:02:50.346
‐ He was gonna die anyway.
Just leave him.

75
00:02:50.370 --> 00:02:51.714
Leave him behind. ‐ Stop it.

76
00:02:51.738 --> 00:02:53.883
We're gonna figure this out.

77
00:02:53.907 --> 00:02:55.385
‐ We gotta be 30 feet down.

78
00:02:55.409 --> 00:02:57.120
I can make it up
to my snowmobile.

79
00:02:57.144 --> 00:02:59.589
I've gotta get my radio.

80
00:02:59.613 --> 00:03:01.758
You can give me a boost
on the ledge.

81
00:03:01.782 --> 00:03:03.092
‐ Yeah.

82
00:03:03.116 --> 00:03:04.293
There's a little piece
of the ledge

83
00:03:04.317 --> 00:03:05.828
you can put your left foot on.
‐ [grunts]

84
00:03:05.852 --> 00:03:06.896
‐ Oh.

85
00:03:06.920 --> 00:03:08.097
‐ [grunts] Okay.

86
00:03:08.121 --> 00:03:09.265
‐ Careful. ‐ [grunts]

87
00:03:09.289 --> 00:03:11.034
‐ There's a pocket there.

88
00:03:11.058 --> 00:03:13.836
‐ [grunts]
‐ She's gonna make it. Harry.

89
00:03:13.860 --> 00:03:15.605
Yes.

90
00:03:15.629 --> 00:03:16.973
Nice one. D'arce.

91
00:03:16.997 --> 00:03:20.510
That's it. That's it. D'arce.

92
00:03:20.534 --> 00:03:21.678
Little to your left.

93
00:03:21.702 --> 00:03:22.912
Left.

94
00:03:22.936 --> 00:03:26.282
‐ This is going to be a problem.

95
00:03:26.306 --> 00:03:29.285
‐ Keep going. ‐ [grunting]

96
00:03:29.309 --> 00:03:31.621
‐ Keep going. You got this.

97
00:03:31.645 --> 00:03:34.057
Yes. ‐ Okay.

98
00:03:34.081 --> 00:03:37.093
‐ My hero.

99
00:03:37.117 --> 00:03:40.096
[dramatic music]

100
00:03:40.120 --> 00:03:43.900
♪ ♪

101
00:03:43.924 --> 00:03:45.325
‐ I'm in!

102
00:03:46.993 --> 00:03:50.339
[ice cracking]

103
00:03:50.363 --> 00:03:51.808
Aah!

104
00:03:51.832 --> 00:03:53.076
‐ Look out!

105
00:03:53.100 --> 00:03:55.778
‐ No! Aah!

106
00:03:55.802 --> 00:03:58.114
[both grunting]

107
00:03:58.138 --> 00:04:02.251
♪ ♪

108
00:04:02.275 --> 00:04:05.054
‐ [sighs] Whoops.

109
00:04:05.078 --> 00:04:07.156
‐ We lost the signal.
[keys clacking]

110
00:04:07.180 --> 00:04:09.625
Whatever the ship
was tethered to is gone.

111
00:04:09.649 --> 00:04:11.651
‐ [sighs]

112
00:04:13.053 --> 00:04:15.765
[sighs]

113
00:04:15.789 --> 00:04:17.533
Okay then.

114
00:04:17.557 --> 00:04:20.036
Time for you two
to get to Colorado

115
00:04:20.060 --> 00:04:23.005
to find me whatever
was flying that machine.

116
00:04:23.029 --> 00:04:29.512
♪ ♪

117
00:04:29.536 --> 00:04:32.506
‐ [moaning]

118
00:04:33.774 --> 00:04:35.918
[heavy breathing]

119
00:04:35.942 --> 00:04:38.454
D'arcy?

120
00:04:38.478 --> 00:04:40.080
Ow.

121
00:04:42.015 --> 00:04:44.227
D'arcy?

122
00:04:44.251 --> 00:04:47.764
D'arcy? D'arcy?

123
00:04:47.788 --> 00:04:50.500
♪ ♪

124
00:04:50.524 --> 00:04:52.635
Harry?

125
00:04:52.659 --> 00:04:55.595
‐ [grunts] ‐ Harry?

126
00:04:57.430 --> 00:04:59.299
‐ [murmurs]

127
00:05:00.967 --> 00:05:02.612
[eerie music]

128
00:05:02.636 --> 00:05:04.638
‐ Harry?

129
00:05:06.106 --> 00:05:08.050
What is that?

130
00:05:08.074 --> 00:05:11.621
‐ [sighs] Don't come any closer.

131
00:05:11.645 --> 00:05:14.557
‐ Are you okay?

132
00:05:14.581 --> 00:05:16.759
‐ [grunts]

133
00:05:16.783 --> 00:05:19.319
‐ [gasps]

134
00:05:21.188 --> 00:05:24.224
What the hell are you?

135
00:05:29.129 --> 00:05:30.129
‐ Don't be afraid.

136
00:05:31.431 --> 00:05:35.044
‐ D'arcy!
‐ I'm not going to hurt you.

137
00:05:35.068 --> 00:05:38.347
‐ [heavy breathing]

138
00:05:38.371 --> 00:05:39.715
Who are you?

139
00:05:39.739 --> 00:05:41.083
‐ Harry.

140
00:05:41.107 --> 00:05:44.921
‐ No. no. no. no.
Half your face is all wrong.

141
00:05:44.945 --> 00:05:46.189
‐ Offensive.

142
00:05:46.213 --> 00:05:48.724
‐ What is happening to you?

143
00:05:48.748 --> 00:05:49.759
‐ Bee sting.

144
00:05:49.783 --> 00:05:51.594
‐ We're inside a glacier.

145
00:05:51.618 --> 00:05:53.029
‐ Snow bees.

146
00:05:53.053 --> 00:05:56.499
I'm allergic
to the sting of snow bees

147
00:05:56.523 --> 00:05:59.602
and ice hornets.

148
00:05:59.626 --> 00:06:01.838
It's bad.

149
00:06:01.862 --> 00:06:03.639
‐ If you don't tell me
what is happening.

150
00:06:03.663 --> 00:06:05.298
I'm going to lose my shit.

151
00:06:06.900 --> 00:06:08.578
‐ Okay.

152
00:06:08.602 --> 00:06:11.814
I am not from this planet.

153
00:06:11.838 --> 00:06:12.915
‐ What?

154
00:06:12.939 --> 00:06:14.917
‐ I am what your people call

155
00:06:14.941 --> 00:06:18.154
an extraterrestrial.

156
00:06:18.178 --> 00:06:19.555
An alien.

157
00:06:19.579 --> 00:06:21.557
♪ ♪

158
00:06:21.581 --> 00:06:25.094
‐ Oh. Oh. I feel nauseous.

159
00:06:25.118 --> 00:06:28.231
‐ You may have a concussion
from the fall.

160
00:06:28.255 --> 00:06:31.834
‐ No. I think it's
the extra‐alien thing

161
00:06:31.858 --> 00:06:34.003
happening in front of me.

162
00:06:34.027 --> 00:06:36.272
‐ Mmm. ‐ D'arcy!

163
00:06:36.296 --> 00:06:39.008
‐ You cannot tell her.
She cannot know.

164
00:06:39.032 --> 00:06:40.142
‐ She's gonna figure it out

165
00:06:40.166 --> 00:06:41.611
when she sees the scales
on your face.

166
00:06:41.635 --> 00:06:44.914
‐ My people do not have scales.

167
00:06:44.938 --> 00:06:47.383
[scoffs] That's racist.

168
00:06:47.407 --> 00:06:49.318
You are thinking
of the Reptilians.

169
00:06:49.342 --> 00:06:51.721
‐ Who?

170
00:06:51.745 --> 00:06:53.155
‐ The Reptilians.

171
00:06:53.179 --> 00:06:56.125
Insidious creatures trying
to take over the universe

172
00:06:56.149 --> 00:06:59.395
by using the Earth
as a laboratory

173
00:06:59.419 --> 00:07:01.597
for hybridization.

174
00:07:01.621 --> 00:07:03.032
‐ D'arcy!

175
00:07:03.056 --> 00:07:05.001
‐ Don't worry.
It will never happen.

176
00:07:05.025 --> 00:07:06.135
They're gross.

177
00:07:06.159 --> 00:07:09.305
They have major hygiene issues.

178
00:07:09.329 --> 00:07:11.741
‐ [sighs] Okay.

179
00:07:11.765 --> 00:07:14.010
Well. if it's not scales. then

180
00:07:14.034 --> 00:07:16.379
why are you growing weird skin?

181
00:07:16.403 --> 00:07:18.881
‐ We have the ability
to mimic other species'

182
00:07:18.905 --> 00:07:22.418
anatomical forms.
but I am too weak.

183
00:07:22.442 --> 00:07:23.953
[sighs]

184
00:07:23.977 --> 00:07:26.355
I'm changing back.

185
00:07:26.379 --> 00:07:28.124
‐ Oh. nope.

186
00:07:28.148 --> 00:07:29.659
‐ Please‐‐ ‐ No!

187
00:07:29.683 --> 00:07:31.661
‐ [sighs]

188
00:07:31.685 --> 00:07:33.195
[grunts]

189
00:07:33.219 --> 00:07:36.198
‐ What is that glowing stuff?

190
00:07:36.222 --> 00:07:37.733
Oh. you're bleeding. aren't you?

191
00:07:37.757 --> 00:07:39.568
‐ Yes.

192
00:07:39.592 --> 00:07:41.470
‐ Aw.

193
00:07:41.494 --> 00:07:48.201
♪ ♪

194
00:07:55.875 --> 00:07:57.453
This is not exactly
how I thought

195
00:07:57.477 --> 00:08:00.113
I'd spend my day.

196
00:08:02.749 --> 00:08:04.660
You know.

197
00:08:04.684 --> 00:08:08.030
you being an alien

198
00:08:08.054 --> 00:08:09.990
sort of explains a lot.

199
00:08:11.725 --> 00:08:13.602
Why are you here?

200
00:08:13.626 --> 00:08:15.438
‐ My ship crashed.

201
00:08:15.462 --> 00:08:17.707
I've been searching
for something I lost

202
00:08:17.731 --> 00:08:20.509
up on this mountain.

203
00:08:20.533 --> 00:08:23.779
‐ What do you mean?
Like. a radio to phone home?

204
00:08:23.803 --> 00:08:25.271
‐ How did you guess?

205
00:08:27.340 --> 00:08:28.918
‐ Uh...

206
00:08:28.942 --> 00:08:32.355
well. all we know of aliens

207
00:08:32.379 --> 00:08:33.356
is from movies.

208
00:08:33.380 --> 00:08:35.658
so it's either a radio
to phone home.

209
00:08:35.682 --> 00:08:39.352
or you're here to kill us...

210
00:08:40.687 --> 00:08:42.331
And eat us.

211
00:08:42.355 --> 00:08:43.599
‐ [laughs]

212
00:08:43.623 --> 00:08:47.136
We do not eat humans.

213
00:08:47.160 --> 00:08:49.305
‐ Okay. ‐ Ha. ha. ha.

214
00:08:49.329 --> 00:08:50.240
‐ [chuckles]

215
00:08:50.264 --> 00:08:52.241
‐ Now can you fix me. please?

216
00:08:52.265 --> 00:08:55.077
‐ Fix you?
I don't even know how you work.

217
00:08:55.101 --> 00:08:57.947
‐ Like you. I have
a closed circulatory system.

218
00:08:57.971 --> 00:09:00.783
So I will bleed out
if you don't stop it.

219
00:09:00.807 --> 00:09:03.786
‐ Okay. Um...

220
00:09:03.810 --> 00:09:05.855
[heavy breathing] Okay.

221
00:09:05.879 --> 00:09:07.113
Let me take a look.

222
00:09:08.314 --> 00:09:09.625
‐ Um...

223
00:09:09.649 --> 00:09:11.127
‐ That part of you
is still a human.

224
00:09:11.151 --> 00:09:12.728
I just touched your penis.

225
00:09:12.752 --> 00:09:14.030
‐ I do not mind it.

226
00:09:14.054 --> 00:09:16.256
It feels good‐‐ ‐ Stop talking.

227
00:09:19.092 --> 00:09:21.037
I think you nicked
an alien artery.

228
00:09:21.061 --> 00:09:23.272
Do you even have arteries?

229
00:09:23.296 --> 00:09:25.141
‐ You need to cauterize
the wound.

230
00:09:25.165 --> 00:09:26.766
Use that.

231
00:09:29.102 --> 00:09:31.971
‐ This? ‐ Mmm.

232
00:09:33.073 --> 00:09:34.650
[grunts]

233
00:09:34.674 --> 00:09:37.386
‐ Oh. Okay.

234
00:09:37.410 --> 00:09:39.179
‐ Yes.

235
00:09:40.914 --> 00:09:42.758
‐ Are you sure about this?

236
00:09:42.782 --> 00:09:44.360
‐ Unlike your delicate species.

237
00:09:44.384 --> 00:09:48.388
my race has an incredibly high
pain threshold.

238
00:09:50.890 --> 00:09:52.492
‐ Okay.

239
00:09:55.595 --> 00:09:58.231
‐ Aah!

240
00:09:59.732 --> 00:10:02.745
‐ [coughs]

241
00:10:02.769 --> 00:10:05.972
[coughing]

242
00:10:08.641 --> 00:10:10.944
Ah! Oh.

243
00:10:14.747 --> 00:10:17.726
[dramatic music]

244
00:10:17.750 --> 00:10:24.700
♪ ♪

245
00:10:24.724 --> 00:10:26.459
Asta!

246
00:10:29.362 --> 00:10:31.207
Asta!

247
00:10:31.231 --> 00:10:32.866
‐ D'arcy!

248
00:10:35.468 --> 00:10:36.679
‐ [chuckles]

249
00:10:36.703 --> 00:10:39.515
‐ Thank God you're okay.

250
00:10:39.539 --> 00:10:40.649
‐ Are you okay?

251
00:10:40.673 --> 00:10:42.885
‐ We're fine!

252
00:10:42.909 --> 00:10:46.412
Everything's... fine.

253
00:10:48.448 --> 00:10:51.026
‐ I'm gonna try to make it
to the top!

254
00:10:51.050 --> 00:10:53.086
Don't move!

255
00:10:54.854 --> 00:10:57.066
‐ D'arcy's gonna call for help.

256
00:10:57.090 --> 00:11:00.269
and by now my dad will know
that I'm missing.

257
00:11:00.293 --> 00:11:02.605
Soon the whole mountain
will be swarming with people

258
00:11:02.629 --> 00:11:05.341
looking for us. ‐ Mmm.

259
00:11:05.365 --> 00:11:07.877
All: Kill the creature!
Catch the beast!

260
00:11:07.901 --> 00:11:10.613
Kill him! Kill the creature!

261
00:11:10.637 --> 00:11:12.248
Catch the beast.

262
00:11:12.272 --> 00:11:14.550
‐ This is bad.

263
00:11:14.574 --> 00:11:17.153
The weaker I get...

264
00:11:17.177 --> 00:11:18.721
‐ The more alien you become?

265
00:11:18.745 --> 00:11:20.589
‐ Mmm.

266
00:11:20.613 --> 00:11:22.758
‐ [sighs]

267
00:11:22.782 --> 00:11:24.517
I see how that
could be a problem.

268
00:11:26.653 --> 00:11:28.063
‐ I hope you understand

269
00:11:28.087 --> 00:11:30.566
that I have lost six chickens
this year to millennials

270
00:11:30.590 --> 00:11:33.068
racing down my road
in their Nazi cars.

271
00:11:33.092 --> 00:11:35.070
I need speed bumps. ‐ Mmm.

272
00:11:35.094 --> 00:11:36.805
‐ Not warnings. I need bumps.

273
00:11:36.829 --> 00:11:38.874
‐ Mmm. ‐ I need big bumps.

274
00:11:38.898 --> 00:11:40.309
‐ Big bumps. yep. ‐ Big bumps.

275
00:11:40.333 --> 00:11:42.178
‐ I am definitely going to look
into this. Mrs. Flaherty.

276
