544
00:23:43.522 --> 00:23:46.835
I really didn't want to live
without her anyway. so...

545
00:23:46.859 --> 00:23:50.438
‐ ♪ Can you set me free? ♪

546
00:23:50.462 --> 00:23:53.308
♪ Can you set me ♪

547
00:23:53.332 --> 00:23:56.211
♪ Can you set me free? ♪

548
00:23:56.235 --> 00:23:58.847
‐ You just try
to climb out of here.

549
00:23:58.871 --> 00:24:00.782
‐ I'm not leaving you.

550
00:24:00.806 --> 00:24:02.550
‐ If you have a choice

551
00:24:02.574 --> 00:24:05.353
between life or death.

552
00:24:05.377 --> 00:24:07.956
you will leave me.

553
00:24:07.980 --> 00:24:11.493
It is you call
survival of the fittest.

554
00:24:11.517 --> 00:24:13.786
‐ You don't have
much faith in people.

555
00:24:15.187 --> 00:24:17.198
‐ Neither do you.

556
00:24:17.222 --> 00:24:20.168
[somber music]

557
00:24:20.192 --> 00:24:21.970
♪ ♪

558
00:24:21.994 --> 00:24:24.539
‐ I used to.

559
00:24:24.563 --> 00:24:25.707
[sighs] Things in life

560
00:24:25.731 --> 00:24:27.976
just didn't work out
the way I wanted.

561
00:24:28.000 --> 00:24:30.679
And I was on a path.
and then I got off a path.

562
00:24:30.703 --> 00:24:32.380
and now I'm just...

563
00:24:32.404 --> 00:24:34.382
trying to find my way again.

564
00:24:34.406 --> 00:24:37.319
‐ Like that monkey movie.

565
00:24:37.343 --> 00:24:39.521
‐ What movie?

566
00:24:39.545 --> 00:24:41.089
"Planet of the Apes"?

567
00:24:41.113 --> 00:24:43.758
‐ The movie about
the flying monkeys.

568
00:24:43.782 --> 00:24:47.095
They are in the trees
living their lives.

569
00:24:47.119 --> 00:24:50.665
and that girl
and that vicious dog

570
00:24:50.689 --> 00:24:54.736
and those other creatures
who had lost their way

571
00:24:54.760 --> 00:24:57.172
from that yellow brick road.
‐ [laughs]

572
00:24:57.196 --> 00:24:59.674
‐ The invade
the monkeys' territory.

573
00:24:59.698 --> 00:25:01.643
‐ You mean "Wizard of Oz"?

574
00:25:01.667 --> 00:25:04.846
‐ Yes. that is it.

575
00:25:04.870 --> 00:25:08.583
‐ Okay. well. the monkeys
are the bad guys.

576
00:25:08.607 --> 00:25:11.319
‐ Not to the monkeys.

577
00:25:11.343 --> 00:25:12.787
‐ Huh.

578
00:25:12.811 --> 00:25:15.724
‐ Can you now go look
for my radio?

579
00:25:15.748 --> 00:25:17.459
[warm music]

580
00:25:17.483 --> 00:25:19.995
‐ I will try to find your radio

581
00:25:20.019 --> 00:25:22.197
so you can get back on
your yellow brick road.

582
00:25:22.221 --> 00:25:23.431
‐ Ah.

583
00:25:23.455 --> 00:25:25.100
‐ You know.

584
00:25:25.124 --> 00:25:27.369
I don't even know
your real name.

585
00:25:27.393 --> 00:25:29.337
‐ It is...

586
00:25:29.361 --> 00:25:32.874
[grunting and clicking]

587
00:25:32.898 --> 00:25:38.003
[unintelligible noises]

588
00:25:39.805 --> 00:25:43.084
My friends call me [hisses].

589
00:25:43.108 --> 00:25:44.886
‐ Okay.

590
00:25:44.910 --> 00:25:47.188
Maybe we should just
stick with Harry.

591
00:25:47.212 --> 00:25:48.914
‐ Mmm.

592
00:25:51.617 --> 00:25:53.695
‐ D'arcy.

593
00:25:53.719 --> 00:25:56.131
Enough rest. Get up now.

594
00:25:56.155 --> 00:25:59.258
‐ [murmurs]

595
00:26:00.159 --> 00:26:02.404
[screaming]

596
00:26:02.428 --> 00:26:04.039
‐ D'arcy. you had a bad fall.

597
00:26:04.063 --> 00:26:06.775
‐ D'arcy. you're gonna need
to get up sometime.

598
00:26:06.799 --> 00:26:07.809
I'll come back in an hour.

599
00:26:07.833 --> 00:26:10.111
‐ Hey. get out bed. bitch.

600
00:26:10.135 --> 00:26:11.713
‐ Asta?

601
00:26:11.737 --> 00:26:13.214
I haven't seen you in forever.

602
00:26:13.238 --> 00:26:16.251
You can't just show up.
I mean. look at me.

603
00:26:16.275 --> 00:26:18.453
I'm a goddamn Lifetime movie.

604
00:26:18.477 --> 00:26:21.556
‐ Okay. Look.

605
00:26:21.580 --> 00:26:24.125
I didn't drive ten hours
to watch you quit.

606
00:26:24.149 --> 00:26:26.494
So get up. ‐ Ow.

607
00:26:26.518 --> 00:26:29.164
‐ You are not quitting.

608
00:26:29.188 --> 00:26:31.132
Okay?

609
00:26:31.156 --> 00:26:32.233
Let's go.

610
00:26:32.257 --> 00:26:33.835
‐ [grunts]

611
00:26:33.859 --> 00:26:36.504
[breathing heavily]

612
00:26:36.528 --> 00:26:39.574
‐ You are not quitting.

613
00:26:39.598 --> 00:26:41.543
‐ I'm not quitting.

614
00:26:41.567 --> 00:26:44.612
[adventurous music]

615
00:26:44.636 --> 00:26:46.948
I'm getting us
the ‐‐‐‐ out of here.

616
00:26:46.972 --> 00:26:48.316
[grunts]

617
00:26:48.340 --> 00:26:49.818
♪ ♪

618
00:26:49.842 --> 00:26:51.119
‐ Don't you get it?

619
00:26:51.143 --> 00:26:53.021
We are running out of time.
all right?

620
00:26:53.045 --> 00:26:54.889
We're out here
in the middle of nowhere

621
00:26:54.913 --> 00:26:57.358
searching for what?
‐ Calm it down now.

622
00:26:57.382 --> 00:27:01.129
‐ I'm just saying. we have no
idea what this thing even is.

623
00:27:01.153 --> 00:27:03.765
or what it can do.
Could be human for all we know.

624
00:27:03.789 --> 00:27:04.999
Could be anybody.

625
00:27:05.023 --> 00:27:08.627
‐ More coffee? ‐ Mmm. love some.

626
00:27:09.595 --> 00:27:12.507
‐ You folks passing through?

627
00:27:12.531 --> 00:27:14.275
‐ Sure are. We just eloped.

628
00:27:14.299 --> 00:27:16.177
Heading to Braddock
to meet my father‐in‐law.

629
00:27:16.201 --> 00:27:17.979
He doesn't know I'm white.
Wish me luck. right?

630
00:27:18.003 --> 00:27:19.547
[laughs]

631
00:27:19.571 --> 00:27:20.748
‐ [laughs]

632
00:27:20.772 --> 00:27:22.750
Well. I'm sure
he'll love you to death.

633
00:27:22.774 --> 00:27:25.253
But you shouldn't linger
too long.

634
00:27:25.277 --> 00:27:26.521
There's a big storm coming.

635
00:27:26.545 --> 00:27:28.590
The pass tends to get shut down.

636
00:27:28.614 --> 00:27:31.493
‐ In that case.
we'll just take the check.

637
00:27:31.517 --> 00:27:34.496
‐ You bet. Drive careful.

638
00:27:34.520 --> 00:27:35.830
‐ I'm just gonna say it.

639
00:27:35.854 --> 00:27:37.699
The General was wrong.
We need backup.

640
00:27:37.723 --> 00:27:39.567
We can't find this thing alone.
‐ Yes. we can.

641
00:27:39.591 --> 00:27:41.836
You said it's tethered to the
ship. so we know it's close.

642
00:27:41.860 --> 00:27:43.872
‐ In a 50‐mile radius.

643
00:27:43.896 --> 00:27:46.207
Do you know how many people
are in a 50‐mile radius?

644
00:27:46.231 --> 00:27:48.042
And that's if it's even
hiding as a human.

645
00:27:48.066 --> 00:27:50.044
What if it's hiding as a tree.
huh?

646
00:27:50.068 --> 00:27:52.580
You wanna just put a bullet
in every tree in the forest?

647
00:27:52.604 --> 00:27:53.815
‐ Most days.

648
00:27:53.839 --> 00:27:56.251
‐ You would say that. Look.

649
00:27:56.275 --> 00:27:58.186
I'm gonna call the military.

650
00:27:58.210 --> 00:28:00.688
‐ You should know me
better by now.

651
00:28:00.712 --> 00:28:02.190
This mission is secretive.

652
00:28:02.214 --> 00:28:04.292
and anyone who doesn't
wanna keep it that way

653
00:28:04.316 --> 00:28:07.162
doesn't live very long.

654
00:28:07.186 --> 00:28:09.264
‐ [grunting]

655
00:28:09.288 --> 00:28:12.667
[gasping]

656
00:28:12.691 --> 00:28:15.670
[dramatic music]

657
00:28:15.694 --> 00:28:18.606
♪ ♪

658
00:28:18.630 --> 00:28:20.508
‐ And you said
we'd never find it.

659
00:28:20.532 --> 00:28:22.410
‐ [gasps]

660
00:28:22.434 --> 00:28:24.670
♪ ♪

661
00:28:30.375 --> 00:28:31.375
[dramatic music]

662
00:28:33.178 --> 00:28:36.357
♪ ♪

663
00:28:36.381 --> 00:28:38.750
‐ [grunts]

664
00:28:42.821 --> 00:28:44.832
[thunder booms]

665
00:28:44.856 --> 00:28:47.468
‐ Hey. it's Asta. I'm not here.

666
00:28:47.492 --> 00:28:50.229
Figure it out. [beeps]

667
00:28:55.767 --> 00:28:57.278
‐ [sighs] I can't find it.

668
00:28:57.302 --> 00:29:00.348
I've looked everywhere.
I think your radio is buried.

669
00:29:00.372 --> 00:29:02.517
‐ I have to find it
before we leave

670
00:29:02.541 --> 00:29:04.152
or else it will be lost forever.

671
00:29:04.176 --> 00:29:06.154
‐ I'm sorry.

672
00:29:06.178 --> 00:29:07.989
Here.

673
00:29:08.013 --> 00:29:10.925
‐ I don't need it.
My planet is freezing.

674
00:29:10.949 --> 00:29:14.062
The cold is actually
helping me recover.

675
00:29:14.086 --> 00:29:15.597
‐ Okay.

676
00:29:15.621 --> 00:29:19.334
Um. well... here you go.

677
00:29:19.358 --> 00:29:21.836
‐ [grunts]

678
00:29:21.860 --> 00:29:23.605
‐ There you go.

679
00:29:23.629 --> 00:29:26.765
[breathing heavily]

680
00:29:28.600 --> 00:29:30.702
Tell me about your planet.

681
00:29:32.571 --> 00:29:34.649
What's it like?

682
00:29:34.673 --> 00:29:36.985
‐ It is magnificent

683
00:29:37.009 --> 00:29:40.788
and brutal like my people.

684
00:29:40.812 --> 00:29:42.557
‐ You know. some native tribes.

685
00:29:42.581 --> 00:29:45.193
they talk about connections

686
00:29:45.217 --> 00:29:47.328
to beings from the stars.

687
00:29:47.352 --> 00:29:49.230
‐ We have been coming here

688
00:29:49.254 --> 00:29:51.332
for thousands of years.

689
00:29:51.356 --> 00:29:53.768
guiding humans.

690
00:29:53.792 --> 00:29:57.405
Stonehenge. the pyramids.

691
00:29:57.429 --> 00:29:59.374
and long before that.

692
00:29:59.398 --> 00:30:01.009
‐ So you're here to help us.

693
00:30:01.033 --> 00:30:04.812
‐ We have always tried to help.

694
00:30:04.836 --> 00:30:07.715
Your people welcomed us
for thousands of years.

695
00:30:07.739 --> 00:30:09.984
but then something changed.

696
00:30:10.008 --> 00:30:14.155
Humans became more fearful
of us.

697
00:30:14.179 --> 00:30:15.757
of each other.

698
00:30:15.781 --> 00:30:19.127
‐ So why did you come this time?

699
00:30:19.151 --> 00:30:21.162
‐ We have been
monitoring changes

700
00:30:21.186 --> 00:30:23.231
to your planet.

701
00:30:23.255 --> 00:30:25.366
‐ How we doing?

702
00:30:25.390 --> 00:30:27.702
‐ Not good.

703
00:30:27.726 --> 00:30:30.772
That is why I need
to find my radio.

704
00:30:30.796 --> 00:30:34.275
so I can ask for help.

705
00:30:34.299 --> 00:30:36.277
‐ When you say not good.

706
00:30:36.301 --> 00:30:39.013
like. how not good?

707
00:30:39.037 --> 00:30:41.716
‐ If a chicken sits on an egg

708
00:30:41.740 --> 00:30:43.785
for the right amount of time.

709
00:30:43.809 --> 00:30:47.288
you get a perfect little chick.

710
00:30:47.312 --> 00:30:48.790
‐ Uh‐huh.

711
00:30:48.814 --> 00:30:52.026
‐ But if you do not care
about the egg.

712
00:30:52.050 --> 00:30:54.762
and you leave it in the sun.

713
00:30:54.786 --> 00:30:56.264
it rots and stinks.

714
00:30:56.288 --> 00:30:58.366
[somber music]

715
00:30:58.390 --> 00:31:00.768
The Earth is the second one.

716
00:31:00.792 --> 00:31:07.432
♪ ♪

717
00:31:11.303 --> 00:31:13.348
‐ Well. I'm gonna go

718
00:31:13.372 --> 00:31:15.040
dig for that radio.

719
00:31:19.211 --> 00:31:20.722
‐ [sighs]

720
00:31:20.746 --> 00:31:22.023
[gentle piano music]

721
00:31:22.047 --> 00:31:24.025
‐ Hmm.

722
00:31:24.049 --> 00:31:25.793
‐ Do you know what you
would like this evening?

723
00:31:25.817 --> 00:31:27.061
‐ Yes. I‐‐ ‐ Sure do.

724
00:31:27.085 --> 00:31:28.996
The lady will have
the chicken paillard.

725
00:31:29.020 --> 00:31:31.666
and I will have the escargot.

726
00:31:31.690 --> 00:31:34.635
‐ Wow. that's very sweet.

727
00:31:34.659 --> 00:31:36.904
You're ordering for me.

728
00:31:36.928 --> 00:31:39.207
I'm going to have the lamb.
‐ Mmm. no. you won't.

729
00:31:39.231 --> 00:31:41.042
She will have
the chicken paillard.

730
00:31:41.066 --> 00:31:42.944
All set. Here you go.

731
00:31:42.968 --> 00:31:45.513
‐ I‐I don't want the chicken.

732
00:31:45.537 --> 00:31:46.914
I'm having the lamb.

733
00:31:46.938 --> 00:31:50.251
‐ [chuckles] I've got this.

734
00:31:50.275 --> 00:31:52.920
♪ ♪

735
00:31:52.944 --> 00:31:54.880
She will have the lamb.

736
00:31:56.548 --> 00:31:57.792
‐ Is something wrong?

737
00:31:57.816 --> 00:31:59.694
Why are you ordering escargot?

738
00:31:59.718 --> 00:32:01.028
You hate snails.

739
00:32:01.052 --> 00:32:04.098
Um. he will have
the steak frites

740
00:32:04.122 --> 00:32:05.767
with the fries extra crispy.

741
00:32:05.791 --> 00:32:07.568
‐ Mmm. nope.
Don't like it. don't want it.

742
00:32:07.592 --> 00:32:09.537
I am having the escargot.

743
00:32:09.561 --> 00:32:11.239
which I love. so.

744
00:32:11.263 --> 00:32:12.740
‐ Okay then.

745
00:32:12.764 --> 00:32:14.709
‐ Thank you.

746
00:32:14.733 --> 00:32:15.943
What was that?

747
00:32:15.967 --> 00:32:18.980
‐ Nothing.
Just‐‐just ordering food.

748
00:32:19.004 --> 00:32:20.281
‐ Kay.

749
00:32:20.305 --> 00:32:21.516
‐ [clears throat]

750
00:32:21.540 --> 00:32:23.217
‐ Sure. thank you.
‐ Yes. please.

751
00:32:23.241 --> 00:32:26.311
‐ La vie en rose.
[both laughing]

752
00:32:30.849 --> 00:32:34.028
[thunder rumbles]

753
00:32:34.052 --> 00:32:36.164
‐ What can I do for you. Dan?

754
00:32:36.188 --> 00:32:38.232
‐ Asta didn't show up
for our weekly dinner date.

755
00:32:38.256 --> 00:32:40.301
and she's not responding
to my calls.

756
00:32:40.325 --> 00:32:42.670
‐ Yeah. well. maybe she stood
you up for a younger fella.

757
00:32:42.694 --> 00:32:43.738
[laughs]

758
00:32:43.762 --> 00:32:46.808
[ominous music]

759
00:32:46.832 --> 00:32:49.243
‐ We were both
in the military. Mike.

760
00:32:49.267 --> 00:32:52.380
When we have a feeling.
we know to trust it.

761
00:32:52.404 --> 00:32:54.615
Something's wrong.

762
00:32:54.639 --> 00:32:56.751
‐ Okay.

763
00:32:56.775 --> 00:32:58.519
All right. I hear you.

764
00:32:58.543 --> 00:33:00.412
[grunts]
Let's see what's going on.

765
00:33:01.847 --> 00:33:03.958
You wanna ride along? ‐ Yes.

766
00:33:03.982 --> 00:33:06.828
‐ Let's hit The 59.

767
00:33:06.852 --> 00:33:09.831
If anybody knows where she is.
it's D'arcy.

768
00:33:09.855 --> 00:33:12.800
‐ [grunting]

769
00:33:12.824 --> 00:33:15.703
[tense music]

770
00:33:15.727 --> 00:33:21.576
♪ ♪

771
00:33:21.600 --> 00:33:22.977
Okay.

772
00:33:23.001 --> 00:33:25.770
Just speed it up. D'arce. Okay.

773
00:33:35.747 --> 00:33:36.747
[elegant music]

774
00:33:38.383 --> 00:33:39.894
♪ ♪

775
00:33:39.918 --> 00:33:41.686
‐ [slurping]

776
00:33:43.121 --> 00:33:45.032
‐ Hey. ‐ Sorry.

777
00:33:45.056 --> 00:33:47.568
‐ Are you okay? ‐ Huh?

778
00:33:47.592 --> 00:33:49.504
‐ You're acting a little weird.

779
00:33:49.528 --> 00:33:51.205
‐ Just enjoying our anniversary

780
00:33:51.229 --> 00:33:53.107
with my lovely wife. [laughs]

781
00:33:53.131 --> 00:33:54.866
‐ [laughs]

782
00:34:01.106 --> 00:34:02.083
‐ Hey. why don't you. uh.

783
00:34:02.107 --> 00:34:03.518
why don't you slide over?

784
00:34:03.542 --> 00:34:06.611
Yeah. scoot. ‐ Oh. okay.

785
00:34:08.713 --> 00:34:10.015
‐ Yeah.

786
00:34:18.690 --> 00:34:20.768
‐ Mmm.

787
00:34:20.792 --> 00:34:22.637
Uh. oh.

788
00:34:22.661 --> 00:34:23.671
‐ What?

789
00:34:23.695 --> 00:34:25.830
‐ You cut your lip on the shell.

790
00:34:27.365 --> 00:34:29.310
‐ Oh.

791
00:34:29.334 --> 00:34:31.770
Now you won't kiss my blood.
It's fine.

792
00:34:33.905 --> 00:34:35.983
‐ What the hell is going on?
‐ Nothing.

793
00:34:36.007 --> 00:34:39.053
I'm just trying to make
our anniversary special.

794
00:34:39.077 --> 00:34:42.456
‐ By picking the restaurant
and ordering for me

795
00:34:42.480 --> 00:34:46.360
and eating escargot.
which you hate?

796
00:34:46.384 --> 00:34:48.829
‐ I‐I thought you'd like it
if I took charge.

797
00:34:48.853 --> 00:34:52.199
I mean. you said the other day
that you wanted me to.

798
00:34:52.223 --> 00:34:53.968
you know. challenge you. [sighs]

799
00:34:53.992 --> 00:34:55.894
‐ Oh. honey.

800
00:34:57.862 --> 00:34:59.640
I did say that.

801
00:34:59.664 --> 00:35:01.375
but this isn't you.

802
00:35:01.399 --> 00:35:03.377
If you wanna pick
the restaurant.

803
00:35:03.401 --> 00:35:05.680
make me go to the taco place

804
00:35:05.704 --> 00:35:08.049
or at least somewhere
that you like.

805
00:35:08.073 --> 00:35:09.483
‐ I do love tacos.

806
00:35:09.507 --> 00:35:11.610
‐ Yeah. and I love you.

807
00:35:12.777 --> 00:35:14.689
We aren't always gonna agree
about everything.

808
00:35:14.713 --> 00:35:18.283
That's okay.
We're different people.

809
00:35:19.451 --> 00:35:21.853
But I want us to be a team.

810
00:35:26.257 --> 00:35:28.536
‐ Hey. John.

811
